From a648f4d9b1bfc6ba0fb9bb98c7a5e67279a3c1ad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: sam mcf <samuel.mcfarlane@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 15 Mar 2026 23:19:28 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] Add write-through session persistence and pre-shutdown memory
 flush
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- run_agent.py: call _flush_messages_to_session_db after each tool-call
  turn (not just at session exit), so messages survive crashes between turns.
  Uses existing _last_flushed_db_idx cursor — idempotent, no duplication.

- gateway/run.py: flush memories for all unflushed sessions in stop()
  before disconnecting adapters, using _async_flush_memories with a 30s
  timeout per session. Prevents context loss on graceful shutdown.

- tests: BDD tests confirming flush is called ≥2× per tool-call conversation,
  and stop() triggers memory flush for sessions not yet captured by the
  expiry watcher.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
